-- Contador Tests Positive for Clenbuterol at Tour de France, is Suspended
-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 2010-09-30T02:14:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-30/contador-tests-positive-for-clenbuterol-at-tour-de-france-is-suspended.html
Alberto Contador tested positive
for the banned substance clenbuterol at the 2010 Tour de France,
cycling’s union said in a press statement.  The Spanish rider, who has won cycling’s most prestigious
title three times, has been provisionally suspended, pending the
outcome of the investigation, the statement said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dex McLuskey at 
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net  